     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To his VVorthy Friend M<seg rend="sup">r</seg>. George Sandys
on his Sacred Poems.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>HOw bold a Worke attempts that Pen</l>
      <l>Which would enrich our Vulgar tongue</l>
      <l>With the high Raptures of those Men</l>
      <l>VVho here with the same Spirit sung</l>
      <l>VVherewith they now assist the Quire</l>
      <l>Of Angels, who their Songs admire?</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>VVhat ever those inspired Soules</l>
      <l>VVere urged to expresse, did shake</l>
      <l>The Aged Deepe, and both the Poles:</l>
      <l>Their numerous Thunder could awake</l>
      <l>Dull Earth, which doth with Heav'n consent</l>
      <l>To all They wrought, and all They meant.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <pb facs="8"/>
      <l>Say (Sacred Bard) what could bestow</l>
      <l>Courage on thee to soare so high?</l>
      <l>Tell mee (Brave Friend) what help'd thee so</l>
      <l>To shake off all Mortalitie?</l>
      <l>To Light this Torch thou hast climb'd higher</l>
      <l>Then he who stole caelestiall Fire.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>Edward Waller.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
